Subject: [PATCH 4/5] Add db migration for hardware health monitoring via
 management interface

This cherry-pick is stripped down to only provide the database migration
from this change, everything else is reverted and will only become
available in 2026.1.

Original commit message:

Add hardware health monitoring via management interface

Adds hardware health status monitoring for baremetal nodes. A new
'health' field on the Node object (API microversion 1.109) exposes
hardware health status reported by the BMC with values 'OK',
'Warning', 'Critical', or None.

Drivers can implement an optional get_node_health() method in their
management interface to retrieve health status. The conductor
automatically queries this during power state synchronization for all
nodes. Drivers without support raise UnsupportedDriverExtension and
are silently skipped.

The Redfish management interface provides the first implementation,
retrieving Status.Health from the System resource.

The feature is enabled by default but can be disabled via the
[conductor]/enable_health_monitoring configuration option.

